The number of games won by five baseball teams are displayed on the graph, but the names of the teams are missing. Here are some clues:

1. The Lions won more games than the Falcons.
2. The Warriors won more games than the Foxes, but fewer games than the Knights.
3. The Foxes won more than 24 games.

How many games did the Warriors win? [asy]
size(150);
defaultpen(linewidth(0.7pt)+fontsize(8));

int i = 1;

draw((0,i*5)--(60,i*5)); ++i;

fill(shift(12,0)*((4,0)--(4,11)--(8,11)--(8,0)--cycle),blue);
draw(shift(12,0)*((4,0)--(4,11)^^(8,0)--(8,11)));
draw((0,i*5)--(60,i*5)); ++i;

fill((4,0)--(4,18)--(8,18)--(8,0)--cycle,blue);
draw((4,0)--(4,18));
draw((8,0)--(8,18));

for(i = 3; i <= 4; ++i)
{
draw((0,i*5)--(60,i*5));
}

fill(shift(24,0)*((4,0)--(4,27)--(8,27)--(8,0)--cycle),blue);
draw(shift(24,0)*((4,0)--(4,27)^^(8,0)--(8,27)));
draw((0,i*5)--(60,i*5)); ++i;

fill(shift(36,0)*((4,0)--(4,33)--(8,33)--(8,0)--cycle),blue);
draw(shift(36,0)*((4,0)--(4,33)^^(8,0)--(8,33)));
draw((0,i*5)--(60,i*5)); ++i;

fill(shift(48,0)*((4,0)--(4,40)--(8,40)--(8,0)--cycle),blue);
draw(shift(48,0)*((4,0)--(4,40)^^(8,0)--(8,40)));
draw((0,i*5)--(60,i*5));
draw((0,i*5)--(60,i*5));

xaxis(Bottom,0,60, RightTicks(" ", N=5, n=1, Size=2));
yaxis(Left,0,45, LeftTicks(Step=5, Size=2));
yaxis(Right,0,45);

label("Baseball Results",(30,50));
label(rotate(90)*"Number of Wins",(-10,22.5));
label("Teams",(30,-10));
for(i = 0; i < 5; ++i)
{
label("?",(6+12*i,-4));
}
[/asy]
